      "score": 13,
      "comments": 31,
      "author": "caius",
      "published": "2026-07-03T09:57:25Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Engineers often use weekends for low-level language exploration, writing custom compilers, or building toolchains in Rust, Zig, or Go.",
        "Homelab maintenance remains a popular weekend task, involving self-hosted services, Kubernetes clusters, Proxmox hypervisors, and local network automation.",
        "Community discussions emphasize balancing active open-source contributions with deliberate downtime to prevent burnout and maintain long-term engineering velocity."
      ]
    },
